Class NodeDataWalrus

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class NodeDataWalrus
extends NodeData

Class representing a Node in Walrus tree. The Walrus tree has a file representation which is very similar to the NCBI tree file representation so NodeDataWalrus is essential the same as NodeDataNCBI with a some extra fields relating to extra data needed in the Walrus tree: new IDs (siblingGroups need to be renumbered) and colouring data. The class is essentially just a data holder.

Author:
Tim Hughes (Computational Biology Unit - University of Bergen - Norway)
